                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>St Louis</placeName>\n                <date>May 7<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1854</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dr Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Your favor has come<lb/> to hand in which I am glad to perceive<lb/>\n                that you are satisfied with my proceeding<add>?</add><lb/> in regard to the\n                remaining Bibles<lb/> I shall make it my Business to see<lb/> those refusing once\n                more. I have to<lb/> say in regard to <persName>Mr Plahto</persName> that the<lb/>\n                man is evidently a Lunatic and<lb/> I should not be surprised if in the<lb/> course\n                of a little time he <sic>his</sic> known<lb/> for an our and out madman<lb/>\n                relative to the remaining Tephilia<lb/> you can charge it to me at $4.00<lb/> one of\n                your subscriber for the Occident<lb/>\n                <persName>John M Myers</persName> leaves here with his<lb/> family for\n                    <placeName>New York</placeName> on the <date>23d</date> of this month<lb/> you\n                will have therefore to send to <placeName>New<lb/> York</placeName> to him I do not\n                know if I<lb/> am call'd upon to do this for I<lb/> thought it would save dispute\n                and<lb/> also a member or subscribe you</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8j63s/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
